Package: EcoHarmony
Title: Taxonomic Harmonisation Tools For Ecological Datasets
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Kurt", "Villsen", , "kurt.villsen1@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package uses a decision-tree framework that standardises each taxonomic lineage in an ecological dataset to a consensus level using a quantitative measure of ambiguity. 
The method compares the number of observations assigned to a focal taxon with those assigned to its descendant taxa and calculates a focal–offspring ratio.
When this ratio exceeds a user-defined threshold, indicating substantial ambiguity, descendant taxa are aggregated to the focal rank.
When the ratio remains below the threshold, finer-resolution identifications are retained. 
Parent-level records are then removed whenever descendants are retained so that each lineage is represented only once in the final dataset.
This framework provides a transparent and reproducible approach for balancing taxonomic resolution against ambiguity. 
